      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KABUKI WARRIORS (4) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at Mandurah over 400m behind Boss Deluxe (23.08) in a Grade 5. Was in the money prior to that. Better than the latest effort and deserves another chance. RAPIDO MYSTIQUE (1) was below best at her last couple, the latest finishing fourth at Mandurah, but was among the placings at Cannington three back. Well placed here and should do much better. FRANTIC PHYLLIS (2) broke well and quickly mustered speed to win over the 509m at this track two runs back then prominent throughout when finishing third at this track last start. Expected to be in this for a long way. REVOLUTION RICO (5) is a last-start placegetter who should be thereabouts.",
